{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775849114691,"sessionID":"ses_28725112effeLv38OgxzcMAJ8A","part":{"id":"prt_d78db085f001ryQsjzHRCtQsM4","messageID":"msg_d78dafdf8001JfyyJUJ5PTSIJm","sessionID":"ses_28725112effeLv38OgxzcMAJ8A","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_1f47572905354d86b79c04bb","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-010/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-010/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-010 вҖ” Router дјҡиҜқз®ЎзҗҶ Tasks\n2: \n3: **Module:** pkg/router  \n4: **Language:** Go  \n5: **Size:** M  \n6: **Stage:** ST-3 (Design Completed)\n7: \n8: ---\n9: \n10: ## Phase 1: Session Configuration\n11: \n12: - [ ] **1.1** Add session config fields to `Config` struct вҖ” `SessionEnabled`, `SessionTimeout`, `SessionCookieName`, `SessionMaxActive`, `SessionCookieSecure`, `SessionCookieHTTPOnly`, `SessionCookieDomain`\n13: - [ ] **1.2** Implement `DefaultConfig()` session defaults вҖ” timeout `30m`, cookie `\"AGENTSESSIONID\"`, max `10000`, cleanup `5m`\n14: - [ ] **1.3** Add session cleanup interval config вҖ” `SessionCleanupInterval` with default `5m`\n15: \n16: ---\n17: \n18: ## Phase 2: Session Data Structures\n19: \n20: - [ ] **2.1** Create `pkg/router/session.go` вҖ” `Session` struct with ID, Backend, CreatedAt, LastActivity, ExpiresAt, Metadata fields\n21: - [ ] **2.2** Create `pkg/router/session.go` вҖ” `SessionStore` interface (Create, Get, Update, Delete, List, Cleanup)\n22: - [ ] **2.3** Implement in-memory `MemorySessionStore` вҖ” thread-safe map with RWMutex\n23: \n24: ---\n25: \n26: ## Phase 3: Session ID Generation\n27: \n28: - [ ] **3.1** Implement `GenerateSessionID()` вҖ” return UUID v4 using `github.com/google/uuid`\n29: - [ ] **3.2** Write unit test: Generate 1000 IDs, verify all unique\n30: - [ ] **3.3** Write unit test: Verify UUID v4 format\n31: \n32: ---\n33: \n34: ## Phase 4: Session Storage Operations\n35: \n36: - [ ] **4.1** Implement `SessionStore.Create()` вҖ” create session with generated ID, backend ref, timestamps\n37: - [ ] **4.2** Implement `SessionStore.Get()` вҖ” retrieve by session ID, return nil if not found\n38: - [ ] **4.3** Implement `SessionStore.Update()` вҖ” update last activity time\n39: - [ ] **4.4** Implement `SessionStore.Delete()` вҖ” remove session by ID\n40: - [ ] **4.5** Implement `SessionStore.List()` вҖ” return all active sessions\n41: - [ ] **4.6** Implement max session limit enforcement вҖ” reject new session when at limit\n42: \n43: ---\n44: \n45: ## Phase 5: Session Middleware\n46: \n47: - [ ] **5.1** Create `pkg/router/session_middleware.go` вҖ” extract session from cookie `AGENTSESSIONID`\n48: - [ ] **5.2** Create `pkg/router/session_middleware.go` вҖ” extract session from header `X-Session-ID`\n49: - [ ] **5.3** Create new session if none found вҖ” generate ID, set response cookie\n50: - [ ] **5.4** Update last activity on each request вҖ” extend expiration on activity\n51: - [ ] **5.5** Integrate middleware into router handler chain\n52: \n53: ---\n54: \n55: ## Phase 6: Session Expiration\n56: \n57: - [ ] **6.1** Implement session expiration check вҖ” mark expired based on `ExpiresAt`\n58: - [ ] **6.2** Implement sliding expiration вҖ” reset `ExpiresAt` on activity\n59: - [ ] **6.3** Reject requests with expired session вҖ” return new session\n60: \n61: ---\n62: \n63: ## Phase 7: Session Cleanup\n64: \n65: - [ ] **7.1** Implement periodic cleanup goroutine вҖ” run every cleanup interval\n66: - [ ] **7.2** Implement `Cleanup()` method вҖ” remove all expired sessions\n67: - [ ] **7.3** Add cleanup to router lifecycle вҖ” start on Start(), stop on Shutdown()\n68: - [ ] **7.4** Write unit test: Verify expired sessions are removed\n69: \n70: ---\n71: \n72: ## Phase 8: Session Affinity (Sticky Sessions)\n73: \n74: - [ ] **8.1** Store backend reference in session вҖ” on new session creation\n75: - [ ] **8.2** Route request to session's assigned backend вҖ” use stored backend key\n76: - [ ] **8.3** Handle backend removal вҖ” invalidate session when backend removed\n77: - [ ] **8.4** Write unit test: Verify same session routes to same backend\n78: \n79: ---\n80: \n81: ## Phase 9: Session Cookie Configuration\n82: \n83: - [ ] **9.1** Set cookie `Secure` flag вҖ” when `SessionCookieSecure: true`\n84: - [ ] **9.2** Set cookie `HttpOnly` flag вҖ” when `SessionCookieHTTPOnly: true`\n85: - [ ] **9.3** Set cookie `Domain` вҖ” when `SessionCookieDomain` configured\n86: - [ ] **9.4** Set cookie `Path` вҖ” default to `/`\n87: \n88: ---\n89: \n90: ## Phase 10: Session Metrics\n91: \n92: - [ ] **10.1** Add `router_sessions_active` gauge вҖ” track active session count\n93: - [ ] **10.2** Add `router_sessions_created_total` counter вҖ” track session creation\n94: - [ ] **10.3** Add `router_sessions_expired_total` counter вҖ” track expiration\n95: - [ ] **10.4** Add `router_session_duration_seconds` histogram вҖ” track session lifetime\n96: - [ ] **10.5** Update metrics on create/expire/cleanup events\n97: \n98: ---\n99: \n100: ## Phase 11: Graceful Shutdown\n101: \n102: - [ ] **11.1** Stop accepting new sessions on shutdown\n103: - [ ] **11.2** Wait for cleanup goroutine to finish\n104: - [ ] **11.3** Ensure existing sessions remain available during shutdown\n105: \n106: ---\n107: \n108: ## Phase 12: Verification\n109: \n110: - [ ] **12.1** `go build ./pkg/router/...` вҖ” successful compilation\n111: - [ ] **12.2** `go test ./pkg/router/... -v` вҖ” all unit tests pass\n112: - [ ] **12.3** Test: Default session config creates store with correct defaults\n113: - [ ] **12.4** Test: Custom session config overrides defaults\n114: - [ ] **12.5** Test: Session middleware extracts from cookie\n115: - [ ] **12.6** Test: Session middleware extracts from header\n116: - [ ] **12.7** Test: New session sets response cookie\n117: - [ ] **12.8** Test: Sticky session routes to same backend\n118: - [ ] **12.9** Test: Session expires after timeout\n119: - [ ] **12.10** Test: Cleanup removes expired sessions\n120: - [ ] **12.11** Test: Metrics reflect session state changes\n121: \n122: ---\n123: \n124: ## Dependencies\n125: \n126: - `github.com/google/uuid` вҖ” Session ID generation\n127: - `github.com/prometheus/client_golang/prometheus` вҖ” Metrics\n128: - AR-009 (completed) вҖ” Router core infrastructure\n129: \n130: ---\n131: \n132: ## References\n133: \n134: - Delta Spec: `changes/AR-010/delta-spec.md`\n135: - Design: `pkg/router/design.md`\n\n(End of file - total 135 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-010 вҖ” Router дјҡиҜқз®ЎзҗҶ Tasks\n\n**Module:** pkg/router  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M  \n**Stage:** ST-3 (Design Completed)\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1: Session Configuration\n\n- [ ] **1.1** Add session config fields to `Config` struct вҖ” `SessionEnabled`, `SessionTimeout`, `SessionCookieName`, `SessionMaxActive`, `SessionCookieSecure`, `SessionCookieHTTPOnly`, `SessionCookieDomain`\n- [ ] **1.2** Implement `DefaultConfig()` session defaults вҖ” timeout `30m`, cookie `\"AGENTSESSIONID\"`, max `10000`, cleanup `5m`\n- [ ] **1.3** Add session cleanup interval config вҖ” `SessionCleanupInterval` with default `5m`\n\n---\n\n## Phase 2: Session Data Structures\n\n- [ ] **2.1** Create `pkg/router/session.go` вҖ” `Session` struct with ID, Backend, CreatedAt, LastActivity, ExpiresAt, Metadata fields","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-010/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775849114663,"end":1775849114688}}}}
