74: | `Router` | HTTP жңҚеҠЎеҷЁз”ҹе‘Ҫе‘Ёжңҹз®ЎзҗҶгҖҒдё»и·Ҝз”ұе…ҘеҸЈ |\n75: | `BackendPool` | еҗҺз«ҜжңҚеҠЎе®һдҫӢжұ з®ЎзҗҶгҖҒеҒҘеә·зҠ¶жҖҒиҝҪиёӘ |\n76: | `RouteHandler` | иҜ·жұӮи·Ҝеҫ„и§ЈжһҗдёҺзӣ®ж ҮеҗҺз«ҜйҖүжӢ© |\n77: | `ProxyHandler` | HTTP/WebSocket иҜ·жұӮиҪ¬еҸ‘ |\n78: | `HealthChecker` | еҗҺз«ҜеҒҘеә·жЈҖжҹҘгҖҒж•…йҡңжЈҖжөӢ |\n79: | `Informer` | Kubernetes CRD зӣ‘еҗ¬гҖҒеҠЁжҖҒжңҚеҠЎеҸ‘зҺ° |\n80: | `Authenticator` | JWT/Bearer Token и®ӨиҜҒ |\n81: | `RateLimiter` | иҜ·жұӮйҖҹзҺҮйҷҗеҲ¶ |\n82: | `Metrics` | Prometheus жҢҮж ҮйҮҮйӣҶ |\n83: \n84: ### 2.3 ж•°жҚ®жөҒ\n85: \n86: ```\n87: 1. е®ўжҲ·з«ҜиҜ·жұӮиҝӣе…Ҙ Router\n88:    в”Ӯ\n89: 2. Authenticator йӘҢиҜҒи®ӨиҜҒдҝЎжҒҜ (JWT/Bearer)\n90:    в”Ӯ\n91: 3. RateLimiter жЈҖжҹҘйҖҹзҺҮйҷҗеҲ¶\n92:    в”Ӯ\n93: 4. RouteHandler и§Јжһҗи·Ҝеҫ„пјҢжҸҗеҸ– namespace/resource\n94:    в”Ӯ\n95: 5. BackendPool ж №жҚ®и·Ҝеҫ„/Header йҖүжӢ©зӣ®ж ҮеҗҺз«Ҝ\n96:    в”Ӯ\n97: 6. HealthChecker жЈҖжҹҘеҗҺз«ҜеҒҘеә·зҠ¶жҖҒ\n98:    в”Ӯ\n99: 7. ProxyHandler иҪ¬еҸ‘иҜ·жұӮеҲ°еҗҺз«Ҝ\n100:    в”Ӯ\n101: 8. Metrics и®°еҪ•иҜ·жұӮжҢҮж Ү\n102:    в”Ӯ\n103: 9. е“Қеә”иҝ”еӣһе®ўжҲ·з«Ҝ\n104: ```\n105: \n106: ---\n107: \n108: ## 3. ж•°жҚ®з»“жһ„\n109: \n110: ### 3.1 ж ёеҝғй…ҚзҪ®\n111: \n112: ```go\n113: // Config holds router configuration\n114: type Config struct {\n115:     // Server settings\n116:     ListenAddress       string        // Listen address (default: \":8080\")\n117:     BackendTimeout      time.Duration // Backend request timeout (default: 30s)\n118:     IdleTimeout         time.Duration // Idle connection timeout (default: 60s)\n119: \n120:     // Health check settings\n121:     HealthCheckInterval time.Duration // Health check interval (default: 10s)\n122:     HealthCheckTimeout  time.Duration // Health check timeout (default: 5s)\n123:     MaxFailures        int           // Max consecutive failures before marking unhealthy (default: 3)\n124: \n125:     // Connection pool settings\n126:     MaxConnsPerBackend  int           // Max connections per backend (default: 100)\n127: \n128:     // Rate limiting\n129:     RateLimitEnabled    bool          // Enable rate limiting (default: false)\n130:     RateLimitRPS        int           // Requests per second (default: 10)\n131:     RateLimitBurst      int           // Burst size (default: 20)\n132: \n133:     // Authentication\n134:     AuthEnabled         bool          // Enable authentication (default: false)\n135:     AuthToken           string        // Bearer token for auth\n136: \n137:     // Kubernetes integration\n138:     WatchNamespaces     []string      // Namespaces to watch (empty = all)\n139:     KubeConfigPath      string        // Path to kubeconfig (optional)\n140:     ResyncPeriod        time.Duration // Informer resync period (default: 30m)\n141: \n142:     // JWT settings\n143:     JWTEnabled         bool          // Enable JWT authentication (default: false)\n144:     JWTSecretName      string        // Kubernetes Secret name for JWT keys (default: \"agentcube-router-identity\")\n145:     JWTNamespace       string        // Secret namespace (default: \"default\")\n146:     JWTExpiration      time.Duration // Token expiration (default: 5m)\n147: }\n148: ```\n149: \n150: ### 3.2 еҗҺз«ҜжңҚеҠЎ\n151: \n152: ```go\n153: // Backend represents a backend service instance\n154: type Backend struct {\n155:     URL                 *url.URL      // Backend URL\n156:     PathPrefix          string        // Path prefix for routing\n157:     Name                string        // Backend name (for logging/metrics)\n158:     Healthy             bool          // Current health status\n159:     ConsecutiveFailures int           // Consecutive failure count\n160:     LastHealthyCheck    time.Time     // Last health check timestamp\n161:    mu                  sync.RWMutex   // Mutex for concurrent access\n162: }\n163: \n164: // BackendPool manages multiple backend instances\n165: type BackendPool struct {\n166:     backends     map[string]*Backend   // key: \"agentruntime/namespace/name\" or \"codeinterpreter/namespace/name\"\n167:     headerRoutes map[string]map[string]string // header-based routing rules\n168:     defaultBackend string               // Default fallback backend\n169:     mu           sync.RWMutex\n170: }\n171: ```\n172: \n173: ### 3.3 д»ЈзҗҶдёҠдёӢж–Ү\n174: \n175: ```go\n176: // ProxyContext holds request context for proxying\n177: type ProxyContext struct {\n178:     Context     context.Context\n179:     Request     *http.Request\n180:     Response    http.ResponseWriter\n181:     Backend     *Backend\n182:     StartTime   time.Time\n183:     RequestID   string\n184:     Namespace   string\n185:     ResourceName string\n186:     ResourceKind string // \"agentruntime\" or \"codeinterpreter\"\n187: }\n188: ```\n189: \n190: ### 3.4 дјҡиҜқз®ЎзҗҶ\n191: \n192: ```go\n193: // SessionInfo represents session state\n194: type SessionInfo struct {\n195:     SessionID     string            // Unique session identifier\n196:     Namespace     string            // Kubernetes namespace\n197:     ResourceName  string            // AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter name\n198:     ResourceKind  string            // \"agentruntime\" or \"codeinterpreter\"\n199:     Endpoint      string            // Backend endpoint URL\n200:     CreatedAt     time.Time         // Session creation time\n201:     LastActivity  time.Time         // Last activity timestamp\n202:     ExpiresAt     time.Time         // Session expiration time\n203:     Labels        map[string]string // Labels from CR\n204:     Status        SessionStatus     // Current status\n205: }\n206: \n207: // SessionStatus enum\n208: type SessionStatus string\n209: \n210: const (\n211:     SessionStatusPending   SessionStatus = \"Pending\"\n212:     SessionStatusActive   SessionStatus = \"Active\"\n213:     SessionStatusIdle     SessionStatus = \"Idle\"\n214:     SessionStatusExpired  SessionStatus = \"Expired\"\n215:     SessionStatusFailed   SessionStatus = \"Failed\"\n216: )\n217: ```\n218: \n219: ### 3.5 JWT з®ЎзҗҶ\n220: \n221: ```go\n222: // JWTManager handles JWT token generation and validation\n223: type JWTManager struct {\n224:     privateKey     *rsa.PrivateKey\n225:     publicKey     *rsa.PublicKey\n226:     clientset     kubernetes.Interface\n227:     secretName    string\n228:     secretNamespace string\n229:     expiration    time.Duration\n230: }\n231: \n232: // JWT claims structure\n233: type JWTClaims struct {\n234:     SessionID    string `json:\"session_id\"`\n235:     Namespace    string `json:\"namespace\"`\n236:     ResourceName string `json:\"resource_name\"`\n237:     ResourceKind string `json:\"resource_kind\"`\n238:     ExpiresAt    int64  `json:\"exp\"`\n239:     IssuedAt     int64  `json:\"iat\"`\n240:     Issuer       string `json:\"iss\"`\n241: }\n242: ```\n243: \n244: ---\n245: \n246: ## 4. API еҗҲзәҰ\n247: \n248: ### 4.1 HTTP з«ҜзӮ№\n249: \n250: | Method | Path | Middleware | Handler |\n251: |--------|------|------------|---------|\n252: | GET | `/health/live` | none | `handleHealthLive` |\n253: | GET | `/health/ready` | none | `handleHealthReady` |\n254: | GET | `/metrics` | none | Prometheus metrics |\n255: | GET | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/*path` | auth, rateLimit, log | `handleAgentRuntimeProxy` |\n256: | POST | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/*path` | auth, rateLimit, log | `handleAgentRuntimeProxy` |\n257: | GET | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/*path` | auth, rateLimit, log | `handleCodeInterpreterProxy` |\n258: | POST | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/*path` | auth, rateLimit, log | `handleCodeInterpreterProxy` |\n259: | WS | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/ws` | auth, rateLimit, log | `handleAgentRuntimeWS` |\n260: | WS | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/ws` | auth, rateLimit, log | `handleCodeInterpreterWS` |\n261: \n262: ### 4.2 д»ЈзҗҶиҜ·жұӮеӨҙ\n263: \n264: | Header | жҸҸиҝ° |\n265: |--------|------|\n266: | `X-Request-ID` | иҜ·жұӮе”ҜдёҖж ҮиҜҶ |\n267: | `X-Forwarded-For` | еҺҹе§Ӣе®ўжҲ·з«Ҝ IP |\n268: | `X-Forwarded-Proto` | еҺҹе§ӢеҚҸи®® (http/https) |\n269: | `X-Real-IP` | зңҹе®һе®ўжҲ·з«Ҝ IP |\n270: | `X-Target-Namespace` | зӣ®ж Ү Kubernetes е‘ҪеҗҚз©әй—ҙ |\n271: | `X-Target-Name` | зӣ®ж Үиө„жәҗеҗҚз§° |\n272: | `X-Target-Kind` | зӣ®ж Үиө„жәҗзұ»еһӢ (agentruntime/codeinterpreter) |\n273: | `X-Session-ID` | дјҡиҜқж ҮиҜҶ (JWT token дёӯзҡ„ session_id) |\n274: \n275: ### 4.3 еҒҘеә·жЈҖжҹҘе“Қеә”\n276: \n277: ```go\n278: // Live check\n279: {\"status\": \"alive\"}\n280: \n281: // Ready check - OK\n282: {\"status\": \"ready\"}\n283: \n284: // Ready check - Not ready\n285: {\"status\": \"not ready\", \"error\": \"informers not synced\"}\n286: \n287: // Metrics endpoint\n288: # Prometheus metrics format\n289: ```\n290: \n291: ### 4.4 й”ҷиҜҜе“Қеә”\n292: \n293: ```json\n294: {\n295:   \"error\": \"error message\",\n296:   \"code\": \"ERR_CODE\",\n297:   \"requestId\": \"req-xxx\"\n298: }\n299: ```\n300: \n301: | Status Code | Description |\n302: |-------------|-------------|\n303: | 200 | Success |\n304: | 400 | Bad Request (invalid path/params) |\n305: | 401 | Unauthorized (invalid/missing token) |\n306: | 404 | Resource not found |\n307: | 429 | Too Many Requests (rate limit) |\n308: | 502 | Bad Gateway (backend error) |\n309: | 503 | Service Unavailable (circuit open/overloaded) |\n310: | 504 | Gateway Timeout (backend timeout) |\n311: \n312: ---\n313: \n314: ## 5. Kubernetes йӣҶжҲҗ\n315: \n316: ### 5.1 Informer й…ҚзҪ®\n317: \n318: ```go\n319: // NewSharedInformerFactory creates informer factory\n320: func NewSharedInformerFactory(client versioned.Interface, resyncPeriod time.Duration) externalversions.SharedInformerFactory\n321: \n322: // Watch AgentRuntime resources\n323: factory.Runtime().V1alpha1().AgentRuntimes().Informer()\n324: \n325: // Watch CodeInterpreter resources\n326: factory.Runtime().V1alpha1().CodeInterpreters().Informer()\n327: ```\n328: \n329: ### 5.2 дәӢд»¶еӨ„зҗҶ\n330: \n331: ```go\n332: // AgentRuntime event handlers\n333: func (i *Informer) AddAgentRuntime(obj *agentcubev1alpha1.AgentRuntime)\n334: func (i *Informer) UpdateAgentRuntime(oldObj, newObj *agentcubev1alpha1.AgentRuntime)\n335: func (i *Informer) DeleteAgentRuntime(obj *agentcubev1alpha1.AgentRuntime)\n336: \n337: // CodeInterpreter event handlers\n338: func (i *Informer) AddCodeInterpreter(obj *agentcubev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter)\n339: func (i *Informer) UpdateCodeInterpreter(oldObj, newObj *agentcubev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter)\n340: func (i *Informer) DeleteCodeInterpreter(obj *agentcubev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter)\n341: ```\n342: \n343: ### 5.3 еҗҺз«ҜжіЁеҶҢйҖ»иҫ‘\n344: \n345: ```\n346: AddAgentRuntime:\n347:   1. жЈҖжҹҘ Status.Phase == \"Running\"\n348:   2. жЈҖжҹҘ Status.Endpoint != \"\"\n349:   3. жһ„йҖ  backend key: \"agentruntime/{namespace}/{name}\"\n350:   4. д»Һ Spec.TargetPorts жҸҗеҸ– PathPrefix (й»ҳи®Ө \"/agent/\")\n351:   5. и°ғз”Ё BackendPool.AddBackend()\n352: \n353: UpdateAgentRuntime:\n354:   1. еҰӮжһңдёҚеҶҚ Running жҲ–ж—  EndpointпјҢи°ғз”Ё RemoveBackend()\n355:   2. еҗҰеҲҷи°ғз”Ё BackendPool.UpdateBackend()\n356: \n357: DeleteAgentRuntime:\n358:   1. и°ғз”Ё RemoveBackend()\n359: ```\n360: \n361: ---\n362: \n363: ## 6. й”ҷиҜҜеӨ„зҗҶ\n364: \n365: ### 6.1 й”ҷиҜҜзұ»еһӢ\n366: \n367: ```go\n368: // Error codes\n369: const (\n370:     ErrCodeBadRequest       = \"ERR_BAD_REQUEST\"\n371:     ErrCodeNotFound         = \"ERR_NOT_FOUND\"\n372:     ErrCodeUnauthorized     = \"ERR_UNAUTHORIZED\"\n373:     ErrCodeTargetNotReady   = \"ERR_TARGET_NOT_READY\"\n374:     ErrCodeProxyFailed      = \"ERR_PROXY_FAILED\"\n375:     ErrCodeTimeout          = \"ERR_TIMEOUT\"\n376:     ErrCodeCircuitOpen      = \"ERR_CIRCUIT_OPEN\"\n377:     ErrCodeRateLimited      = \"ERR_RATE_LIMITED\"\n378:     ErrCodeInternalError    = \"ERR_INTERNAL\"\n379: )\n380: \n381: // RouterError represents a router-specific error\n382: type RouterError struct {\n383:     Code       string\n384:     Message    string\n385:     StatusCode int\n386:     Err        error\n387: }\n388: ```\n389: \n390: ### 6.2 й”ҷиҜҜеӨ„зҗҶзӯ–з•Ҙ\n391: \n392: | й”ҷиҜҜеңәжҷҜ | еӨ„зҗҶзӯ–з•Ҙ |\n393: |----------|----------|\n394: | и®ӨиҜҒеӨұиҙҘ | иҝ”еӣһ 401пјҢи®°еҪ•й”ҷиҜҜжҢҮж Ү |\n395: | иө„жәҗдёҚеӯҳеңЁ (404) | иҝ”еӣһ 404пјҢдёҚйҮҚиҜ• |\n396: | йҖҹзҺҮи¶…йҷҗ | иҝ”еӣһ 429пјҢжҸҗзӨәе®ўжҲ·з«ҜйҖҖйҒҝ |\n397: | еҗҺз«Ҝи¶…ж—¶ | и®°еҪ•еӨұиҙҘпјҢйҮҚиҜ•дёҖж¬ЎпјҢеӨұиҙҘеҲҷзҶ”ж–ӯ |\n398: | еҗҺз«ҜиҝһжҺҘеӨұиҙҘ | зҶ”ж–ӯи®Ўж•°пјҢиҫҫеҲ°йҳҲеҖјеҗҺж Үи®°дёҚеҒҘеә· |\n399: | зҶ”ж–ӯеҷЁејҖеҗҜ | иҝ”еӣһ 503пјҢе®ҡжңҹе°қиҜ•жҒўеӨҚ |\n400: | еҶ…йғЁй”ҷиҜҜ | иҝ”еӣһ 500пјҢи®°еҪ•й”ҷиҜҜж—Ҙеҝ— |\n401: \n402: ### 6.3 ж—Ҙеҝ—и§„иҢғ\n403: \n404: ```go\n405: // Structured logging with fields\n406: log.Info(\"Request processed\",\n407:     \"requestId\", requestID,\n408:     \"method\", method,\n409:     \"path\", path,\n410:     \"namespace\", namespace,\n411:     \"resourceName\", resourceName,\n412:     \"backend\", backendName,\n413:     \"latency\", latency,\n414:     \"statusCode\", statusCode,\n415: )\n416: ```\n417: \n418: ---\n419: \n420: ## 7. жөӢиҜ•зӯ–з•Ҙ\n421: \n422: ### 7.1 еҚ•е…ғжөӢиҜ•\n423: \n424: | жЁЎеқ— | жөӢиҜ•йҮҚзӮ№ |\n425: |------|----------|\n426: | `BackendPool` | е№¶еҸ‘е®үе…ЁгҖҒи·Ҝз”ұйҖүжӢ©гҖҒеҒҘеә·зҠ¶жҖҒз®ЎзҗҶ |\n427: | `RouteHandler` | и·Ҝеҫ„и§ЈжһҗгҖҒHeader и·Ҝз”ұгҖҒеҗҺз«ҜйҖүжӢ© |\n428: | `ProxyHandler` | URL йҮҚеҶҷгҖҒHeader и®ҫзҪ®гҖҒиҝһжҺҘжұ з®ЎзҗҶ |\n429: | `HealthChecker` | еҒҘеә·жЈҖжҹҘи§ҰеҸ‘гҖҒзҠ¶жҖҒиҪ¬жҚўгҖҒеӨұиҙҘи®Ўж•° |\n430: | `Authenticator` | Token йӘҢиҜҒгҖҒMiddleware жөҒзЁӢ |\n431: | `RateLimiter` | йҖҹзҺҮйҷҗеҲ¶гҖҒе№¶еҸ‘е®үе…ЁгҖҒMiddleware жөҒзЁӢ |\n432: | `Metrics` | жҢҮж Үи®°еҪ•гҖҒж ҮзӯҫжӯЈзЎ®жҖ§ |\n433: \n434: ### 7.2 йӣҶжҲҗжөӢиҜ•\n435: \n436: ```go\n437: // дҪҝз”Ё fake client-go иҝӣиЎҢйӣҶжҲҗжөӢиҜ•\n438: import (\n439:     \"k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes/fake\"\n440:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/clientset/versioned/fake\"\n441: )\n442: \n443: func TestRouterWithFakeClients(t *testing.T) {\n444:     // Setup fake clients\n445:     kubeClient := fake.NewSimpleClientset()\n446:     runtimeClient := clientsetfake.NewSimpleClientset()\n447: \n448:     // Create informer factory\n449:     informerFactory := externalversions.NewSharedInformerFactory(runtimeClient, 30*time.Minute)\n450: \n451:     // Create router with fake clients\n452:     router := NewRouter(&Config{\n453:         WatchNamespaces: []string{\"default\"},\n454:     })\n455: \n456:     // Add test AgentRuntime\n457:     ar := &agentcubev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n458:         ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n459:             Name:      \"test-runtime\",\n460:             Namespace: \"default\",\n461:         },\n462:         Status: agentcubev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeStatus{\n463:             Phase:    agentcubev1alpha1.PhaseRunning,\n464:             Endpoint: \"http://localhost:8081\",\n465:         },\n466:     }\n467:     runtimeClient.AgentRuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(\"default\").Create(context.Background(), ar, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n468: \n469:     // Start informers\n470:     informerFactory.Start(nil)\n471:     informerFactory.WaitForCacheSync(nil)\n472: \n473:     // Test proxy flow\n474:     req := httptest.NewRequest(\"GET\", \"/v1/namespaces/default/agent-runtimes/test-runtime/api\", nil)\n475:     w := httptest.NewRecorder()\n476:     router.ServeHTTP(w, req)\n477: \n478:     assert.Equal(t, http.StatusOK, w.Code)\n479: }\n480: ```\n481: \n482: ### 7.3 жөӢиҜ•еңәжҷҜ\n483: \n484: | еңәжҷҜ | йў„жңҹз»“жһң |\n485: |------|----------|\n486: | жӯЈеёёд»ЈзҗҶжөҒзЁӢ | иҜ·жұӮжҲҗеҠҹиҪ¬еҸ‘пјҢеҗҺз«Ҝе“Қеә”жӯЈзЎ®иҝ”еӣһ |\n487: | еҗҺз«ҜеҠЁжҖҒж·»еҠ  | Informer дәӢд»¶и§ҰеҸ‘пјҢеҗҺз«ҜиҮӘеҠЁеҠ е…Ҙи·Ҝз”ұ |\n488: | еҗҺз«ҜеҠЁжҖҒеҲ йҷӨ | Informer дәӢд»¶и§ҰеҸ‘пјҢеҗҺз«Ҝд»Һи·Ҝз”ұз§»йҷӨ |\n489: | еҒҘеә·жЈҖжҹҘеӨұиҙҘ | иҝһз»ӯеӨұиҙҘ 3 ж¬ЎеҗҺж Үи®°дёәдёҚеҒҘеә·пјҢжөҒйҮҸеҲҮжҚў |\n490: | и®ӨиҜҒеӨұиҙҘ | иҝ”еӣһ 401пјҢиҜ·жұӮдёҚиҪ¬еҸ‘ |\n491: | йҖҹзҺҮи¶…йҷҗ | иҝ”еӣһ 429пјҢиҜ·жұӮдёҚиҪ¬еҸ‘ |\n492: | еҗҺз«Ҝи¶…ж—¶ | йҮҚиҜ•дёҖж¬ЎпјҢеӨұиҙҘиҝ”еӣһ 504 |\n493: | WebSocket иҝһжҺҘ | й•ҝиҝһжҺҘдҝқжҢҒпјҢеҸҢеҗ‘йҖҡдҝЎжӯЈеёё |\n494: \n495: ### 7.4 жөӢиҜ•иҰҶзӣ–зҺҮзӣ®ж Ү\n496: \n497: | з»„д»¶ | зӣ®ж ҮиҰҶзӣ–зҺҮ |\n498: |------|-----------|\n499: | server.go | 80% |\n500: | backend.go | 85% |\n501: | route.go | 85% |\n502: | proxy.go | 80% |\n503: | health.go | 85% |\n504: | informer.go | 80% |\n505: | auth.go | 90% |\n506: | ratelimit.go | 90% |\n507: | metrics.go | 85% |\n508: \n509: ---\n510: \n511: ## 8. е…ій”®жҺҘеҸЈе®ҡд№ү\n512: \n513: ### 8.1 Router жҺҘеҸЈ\n514: \n515: ```go\n516: type Router interface {\n517:     // Start begins serving HTTP requests\n518:     Start() error\n519: \n520:     // Stop gracefully shuts down the router\n521:     Stop(ctx context.Context) error\n522: \n523:     // AddBackend adds a backend to the pool\n524:     AddBackend(key, endpoint, pathPrefix, name string) error\n525: \n526:     // RemoveBackend removes a backend from the pool\n527:     RemoveBackend(key string)\n528: \n529:     // GetConfig returns current configuration\n530:     GetConfig() *Config\n531: \n532:     // GetMetrics returns current metrics\n533:     GetMetrics() *Metrics\n534: }\n535: ```\n536: \n537: ### 8.2 ServiceDiscoverer жҺҘеҸЈ\n538: \n539: ```go\n540: type ServiceDiscoverer interface {\n541:     // Start starts the informer\n542:     Start() error\n543: \n544:     // Stop stops the informer\n545:     Stop()\n546: \n547:     // GetEndpoint returns endpoint for given namespace and name\n548:     GetEndpoint(namespace, name, kind string) (string, error)\n549: }\n550: ```\n551: \n552: ### 8.3 ProxyHandler жҺҘеҸЈ\n553: \n554: ```go\n555: type ProxyHandler interface {\n556:     // ServeHTTP proxies the request to backend\n557:     ServeHTTP(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request, backend *Backend)\n558: \n559:     // GetTransport returns the underlying HTTP transport\n560:     GetTransport() *http.Transport\n561: }\n562: ```\n563: \n564: ---\n565: \n566: ## 9. зӣ‘жҺ§жҢҮж Ү\n567: \n568: ### 9.1 Prometheus жҢҮж Ү\n569: \n570: | Metric | Type | Labels | Description |\n571: |--------|------|--------|-------------|\n572: | `router_request_duration_seconds` | Histogram | method, path, backend | Request duration |\n573: | `router_backend_requests_total` | Counter | backend, status | Backend request count |\n574: | `router_backend_healthy` | Gauge | backend | Backend health status (1/0) |\n575: | `router_errors_total` | Counter | type | Error count by type |\n576: | `router_rate_limit_rejected_total` | Counter | client_ip | Rate limited requests |\n577: | `router_active_connections` | Gauge | backend | Active connections per backend |\n578: | `router_informer_sync_total` | Counter | resource_type | Informer sync count |\n579: \n580: ### 9.2 еҒҘеә·жЈҖжҹҘз«ҜзӮ№\n581: \n582: - `/health/live` вҖ” Liveness probe (always returns 200 if process is running)\n583: - `/health/ready` вҖ” Readiness probe (returns 200 only if informers are synced and backend pool is initialized)\n584: \n585: ---\n586: \n587: ## 10. е®һж–Ҫи®ЎеҲ’\n588: \n589: ### Phase 1: ж ёеҝғеҠҹиғҪ\n590: - [ ] е®Ңе–„ Router дё»з»“жһ„\n591: - [ ] е®һзҺ° BackendPool зҡ„зәҝзЁӢе®үе…Ёж“ҚдҪң\n592: - [ ] е®һзҺ°еҹәзЎҖд»ЈзҗҶиҪ¬еҸ‘\n593: \n594: ### Phase 2: Kubernetes йӣҶжҲҗ\n595: - [ ] е®һзҺ° Informer е®Ңж•ҙеҠҹиғҪ\n596: - [ ] йӣҶжҲҗ client-go иҝӣиЎҢ CRD зӣ‘еҗ¬\n597: - [ ] е®һзҺ° Add/Update/Delete дәӢд»¶еӨ„зҗҶ\n598: \n599: ### Phase 3: дјҡиҜқз®ЎзҗҶ\n600: - [ ] е®һзҺ° JWT Token з”ҹжҲҗе’ҢйӘҢиҜҒ\n601: - [ ] е®һзҺ°дјҡиҜқзҠ¶жҖҒиҝҪиёӘ\n602: - [ ] е®һзҺ°еҹәдәҺ session зҡ„и·Ҝз”ұ\n603: \n604: ### Phase 4: еҸҜйқ жҖ§\n605: - [ ] е®Ңе–„еҒҘеә·жЈҖжҹҘйҖ»иҫ‘\n606: - [ ] е®һзҺ°зҶ”ж–ӯжңәеҲ¶\n607: - [ ] ж·»еҠ и¶…ж—¶жҺ§еҲ¶\n608: \n609: ### Phase 5: еҸҜи§ӮжөӢжҖ§\n610: - [ ] е®Ңе–„ж—Ҙеҝ—з»“жһ„еҢ–\n611: - [ ] ж·»еҠ е®Ңж•ҙ Prometheus жҢҮж Ү\n612: - [ ] е®һзҺ°еҒҘеә·жЈҖжҹҘз«ҜзӮ№\n613: \n614: ---\n615: \n616: ## 11. дҫқиө–\n617: \n618: ### 11.1 еӨ–йғЁдҫқиө–\n619: \n620: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n621: |---------|---------|---------|\n622: | `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | ^1.9.0 | HTTP framework |\n623: | `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | ^5.0.0 | JWT token handling |\n624: | `github.com/prometheus/client_golang/prometheus` | ^1.16.0 | Metrics |\n625: | `golang.org/x/time/rate` | ^0.5.0 | Rate limiting |\n626: | `k8s.io/client-go` | ^0.34.0 | Kubernetes client |\n627: | `k8s.io/apimachinery` | ^0.34.0 | API types |\n628: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | ^2.100.0 | Logging |\n629: \n630: ### 11.2 еҶ…йғЁдҫқиө–\n631: \n632: | Module | Purpose |\n633: |--------|---------|\n634: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Generated Kubernetes typed client |\n635: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` | CRD types |\n636: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/client/listers` | Resource listers |\n637: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/client/informers` | Shared informers |\n638: \n639: ---\n640: \n641: ## 12. еҸӮиҖғ\n642: \n643: - [AR-009: Router HTTP еҸҚеҗ‘д»ЈзҗҶж ёеҝғ](design.md)\n644: - [Session Routing Design](session-routing/design.md)\n645: - [client-go library](deployment/client-go.md)\n646: - [Kubernetes Informer Pattern](https://medium.com/@cloud_eng/kubernetes-informers-the-magic-behind-operator-frameworks-2c4e3a87a9c3)\n\n(End of file - total 646 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-010 вҖ” Router дјҡиҜқз®ЎзҗҶ\n\n- **AR ID**: AR-010\n- **Module**: `pkg/router`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: M\n- **Status**: Draft\n\n## 1. жҰӮиҝ°\n\n`pkg/router` жҳҜ agentcube зҡ„ HTTP еҸҚеҗ‘д»ЈзҗҶж ёеҝғжЁЎеқ—пјҢиҙҹиҙЈе°ҶеӨ–йғЁ HTTP иҜ·жұӮи·Ҝз”ұеҲ°еҗҺз«Ҝзҡ„ AgentRuntime е’Ң CodeInterpreter е®һдҫӢгҖӮжң¬и®ҫи®Ўж–ҮжЎЈиҒҡз„ҰдәҺ**дјҡиҜқз®ЎзҗҶ**пјҲSession ManagementпјүеҠҹиғҪпјҢеҹәдәҺе·Іжңүзҡ„еҸҚеҗ‘д»ЈзҗҶиғҪеҠӣпјҢеўһеҠ еҜ№дјҡиҜқз”ҹе‘Ҫе‘ЁжңҹгҖҒзҠ¶жҖҒиҝҪиёӘгҖҒJWT и®ӨиҜҒе’ҢеҠЁжҖҒжңҚеҠЎеҸ‘зҺ°зҡ„ж”ҜжҢҒгҖӮ\n\n### 1.1 зӣ®ж Ү\n\n- е®һзҺ°еҹәдәҺ Kubernetes CRD зҡ„еҠЁжҖҒеҗҺз«ҜжңҚеҠЎеҸ‘зҺ°\n- ж”ҜжҢҒдјҡиҜқз”ҹе‘Ҫе‘Ёжңҹз®ЎзҗҶпјҲеҲӣе»әгҖҒжӣҙж–°гҖҒй”ҖжҜҒпјү\n- жҸҗдҫӣ JWT д»ӨзүҢи®ӨиҜҒе’ҢжҺҲжқғ\n- йӣҶжҲҗ client-go иҝӣиЎҢ Kubernetes API дәӨдә’\n- жҸҗдҫӣеҸҜи§ӮжөӢжҖ§пјҲPrometheus жҢҮж ҮгҖҒеҒҘеә·жЈҖжҹҘпјү\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/router/design.md","time":{"start":1775849168126,"end":1775849168145}}}}
